name: Andrew Elliott McBurney
tweet: Mass murder and attempted mass murder are never random, even though the victims may be.  What is still not discussed enough, is that, whatever other motivations they may have, most mass shooters do have something in common--they're men who have a problem with women.

name: Andrew Elliott McBurney
tweet: Kids: First, of course, we hope everyone is okay and that those with critical injuries recover.  So, about the word "random" in the context of attempted mass murder. It's used to mean the shooter didn't care whom he or she killed; however, a shooter's motivation is never random.

name: Andrew Elliott McBurney
tweet: Kids: Here's what I want to say about this--something is a crime if it's defined in federal law or state penal codes as a crime. There are few common law crimes left, and saying the Pledge or part of the Pledge in the language of your religion isn't one of them.
